definitions.definition: An alloy of copper and tin, similar to bronze , with a sufficient portion of tin to make it a pewter-like color with yellowish tinge (rather than the brownish-gold color of bronze of higher copper content), once used in thin sheets and for domestic utensils and light-duty tools.
Sheet tin; iron plate, covered with tin.

main_definition: ( archaic or historical ) An alloy of copper and tin, similar to bronze , with a sufficient portion of tin to make it a pewter-like color with yellowish tinge (rather than the brownish-gold color of bronze of higher copper content), once used in thin sheets and for domestic utensils and light-duty tools.
secondary_definitions: Sheet tin; iron plate, covered with tin.
